**Description:** **: This script is a Python program that integrates Ollama (a local AI model) with the Wayback Machine tools to allow users to interact with archived web content. It defines a class called OllamaToolUser, which initializes with a model name and handles tasks such as generating AI responses, normalizing URLs, executing tools (e.g., retrieving archived snapshots or capture history), formatting results, and running user interactions. The script includes a main function that provides a command-line interface for users to input queries like searching for URLs, getting history, or viewing snapshots. Its purpose is to facilitate easy access to Wayback Machine features via an AI-powered tool, handling errors, JSON parsing, and user inputs in a loop until the user quits.

